Woozle Hypertwin:

"authority hysteresis: the degree to which a governance structure enforces the continuance of authority in the absence of legitimate support.

We need governance structures that minimize authority hysteresis and therefore do not create concentrations of unaccountable power -- while still positively correlating good decisionmaking ability with decisionmaking influence.﻿"
